name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: dfs.namenode.fs-limits.min-block-size
description:
Minimum block size in bytes, enforced by the Namenode at create
      time. This prevents the accidental creation of files with tiny block
      sizes (and thus many blocks), which can degrade performance. Support multiple
      size unit suffix(case insensitive), as described in dfs.blocksize.

name: fs.du.interval
description: File space usage statistics refresh interval in msec.

name: yarn.app.mapreduce.client-am.ipc.max-retries-on-timeouts
description:
The number of client retries on socket timeouts to the AM - before
    reconnecting to the RM to fetch Application Status.
    In other words, it is the ipc.client.connect.max.retries.on.timeouts to be used during
    reconnecting to the RM and fetching Application Status.

name: dfs.datanode.data.transfer.bandwidthPerSec
description:
Specifies the maximum amount of bandwidth that the data transfering can utilize for transfering block when
      BlockConstructionStage is
      PIPELINE_SETUP_CREATE and clientName is empty.
      When the bandwidth value is zero, there is no limit.

name: dfs.qjournal.new-epoch.timeout.ms
description:
Timeout in milliseconds when getting an epoch number for write
    access to JournalNodes.

name: dfs.namenode.blockreport.queue.size
description: The queue size of BlockReportProcessingThread in BlockManager.
